Cape Town and surrounding areas have been hit by cold, wet and windy weather. The weather service forecasts this will last for a few days. The bone-chilling conditions also mean we will see snow on Western Cape mountains. Courtesy #DsTV403 CAPE TOWN - Cape Town and surrounding areas have been bitten by cold, wet and windy weather. READ: Snow falls in Lesotho, Eastern Cape The weather service forecasts this will last for a few days. READ: Parts of SA turned into winter wonderland The bone-chilling conditions mean snow will be seen on the Western Cape mountains. The Matroosberg Nature Reserve near Ceres is blanketed in white after fresh snowfalls. eNCA's Monique Mortlock has more details in the video above.